com.zebra.sdk.common.card.job

Interface JobControlProvider

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ZebraCardPrinter, ZebraPrinterZmotif, ZebraPrinterZxp

    public interface JobControlProvider
    Interface implemented by jobControl that provides access to job related settings.

    • Method Detail

      • getJobSettings

        java.util.Set<String> getJobSettings()
                                     throws SettingsException
        Retrieve all of the setting identifiers for a printer.
        • Note These are the IDs that may be used as keys for retrieving and updating settings for a device.
        Returns:
        a Set of identifiers available for a device.
        Throws:
        SettingsException - if the setting IDs could not be loaded.

      • getJobSettingValue

        String getJobSettingValue(String settingId)
                          throws SettingsException
        Retrieves the printer's setting value for a specific setting ID.
        Parameters:
        settingId - the setting ID for the setting you want to retrieve.
        Returns:
        the setting's value.
        Throws:
        SettingsException - if the setting could not be retrieved or there is an error communicating with the printer.

      • getJobSettingsValues

        java.util.Map<String,String> getJobSettingsValues(java.util.List<String> listOfSettings)
                                                  throws SettingsException
        Retrieves the printer's setting values for a list of setting IDs.
        Parameters:
        listOfSettings - a list of setting IDs for the settings you want to retrieve.
        Returns:
        a Map containing the setting IDs their values.
        • Key = The setting ID.
        • Value = The setting value.
        Throws:
        SettingsException - if the settings could not be retrieved or there is an error communicating with the printer.

      • getAllJobSettingValues

        java.util.Map<String,String> getAllJobSettingValues()
                                                    throws SettingsException
        Retrieves all of the printer's setting values.
        Returns:
        a Map containing the printer's IDs and values of all the settings provided by the printer.
        • Key = The setting ID.
        • Value = The setting value.
        Throws:
        SettingsException - if the settings could not be retrieved or there is an error communicating with the printer.

      • getAllJobSettings

        java.util.Map<String,Setting> getAllJobSettings()
                                                throws SettingsException
        Retrieve all settings and their attributes.
        Returns:
        a Map of job setting IDs and setting attributes contained in the profile.
        Throws:
        SettingsException - if the settings could not be retrieved.

      • setJobSettings

        void setJobSettings(java.util.Map<String,String> settingValuePairs)
                    throws SettingsException
        Sets a set of the printer's settings to their given values.
        Parameters:
        settingValuePairs - a Map containing the setting's ID and the new value for the setting.
        • Key = The setting ID.
        • Value = The setting value.
        Throws:
        SettingsException - if any of the settings are read only, do not exist, or could not be set.

        Returns:

        Throws:
        SettingsException - if the setting does not exist or the setting's range could not be retrieved.
